#Reading Datasets
BetData=readRDS("C:\\Users\\burhan\\Desktop\\ETM 58D\\ETM 58D\\R (2)\\R\\df9b1196-e3cf-4cc7-9159-f236fe738215_odd_details.rds")
MatchesData=readRDS("C:\\Users\\burhan\\Desktop\\ETM 58D\\ETM 58D\\R (2)\\R\\df9b1196-e3cf-4cc7-9159-f236fe738215_matches.rds")


#Manupulating Matches data

MatchesData[,c("HomeScore","AwayScore"):=tstrsplit(score,":")]
MatchesData[,HomeScore:=as.numeric(HomeScore)]
## Warning in eval(jsub, SDenv, parent.frame()): Zorlamadan dolayı ortaya
## çıkan NAs
MatchesData[,AwayScore:=as.numeric(AwayScore)]
MatchesData[,totalgoals:=(HomeScore+AwayScore)]
MatchesData[,Over2.5:=ifelse(totalgoals>2.5,1,0)]
MatchesData[,score:=NULL]
MatchesData$Over2.5=as.factor(MatchesData$Over2.5)
MatchesData=MatchesData[complete.cases(MatchesData)]

#Selection of bookmakers,taking their final odds, dcast the table and merge it with mathces dataset to get the table  prepared for PCA and MDS
DataofSelectedBookmakers=BetData[bookmaker %in% c("Betway","bet365","Interwetten","Betclic","Pinnacle")]

PooledData=DataofSelectedBookmakers[order(matchId,betType,oddtype,bookmaker,date)]
PooledData2=PooledData[,list(final=odd[.N]),by=list(matchId,betType,oddtype,bookmaker)]

DcastedPooledData=dcast(PooledData2, matchId~betType+oddtype+bookmaker ,value.var="final")
DcastedPooledData2=DcastedPooledData[complete.cases(DcastedPooledData)]

MergedDcastedPooledData=merge(DcastedPooledData2,MatchesData[,list(matchId,Over2.5)],by=c("matchId"),all.x=TRUE)
MergedDcastedPooledData=MergedDcastedPooledData[complete.cases(MergedDcastedPooledData)]

#Principle COmponent Analisis 
PooledPCA= prcomp(MergedDcastedPooledData[,c(2:51)], center = TRUE,scale = TRUE)
summary(PooledPCA)

# MDS with Euclidean distance
EuclidDist=dist(MergedDcastedPooledData[,c(2:51)])
fit= cmdscale(EuclidDist,eig=TRUE, k=50) 

# MDS with Manhattan distance
ManhatDist=dist(MergedDcastedPooledData[,c(2:51)],method="manhattan") 
fit2=cmdscale(ManhatDist,eig=TRUE, k=50) 


# Plot solution of MDS with Euclidean Distance
x = fit$points[,1]
y = fit$points[,2]
plot(x, y, xlab="Coordinate 1", ylab="Coordinate 2", 
  main="Metric MDS", type="n")
text(x, y, labels = colnames(MergedDcastedPooledData[,c(2:51)]), cex=.7)

# Plot solution of MDS with Manhattan Distance
x = fit2$points[,1]
y = fit2$points[,2]
plot(x, y, xlab="Coordinate 1", ylab="Coordinate 2", 
  main="Metric MDS", type="n")
text(x, y, labels = colnames(MergedDcastedPooledData[,c(2:51)]), cex=.7)

#Bind first 2 MDS components to the datatable
MDSBindedPooledEuc=cbind(MergedDcastedPooledData,fit$points[,1:2])
MDSBindedPooledManhat=cbind(MergedDcastedPooledData,fit2$points[,1:2])

#Changing Column Names
colnames(MDSBindedPooledEuc)[colnames(MDSBindedPooledEuc)=="V1"] = "MDS1"
colnames(MDSBindedPooledEuc)[colnames(MDSBindedPooledEuc)=="V2"] = "MDS2"
colnames(MDSBindedPooledManhat)[colnames(MDSBindedPooledManhat)=="V2"] = "MDS2"
colnames(MDSBindedPooledManhat)[colnames(MDSBindedPooledManhat)=="V1"] = "MDS1"

#Plot for Over-Under results
##Euclidean
PooledMSDEuc=ggplot(MDSBindedPooledEuc,aes(MDS1,MDS2,col=Over2.5,fill=Over2.5))+

geom_point(shape=21,col="black")

geom_point(shape=21,col="black")
